  "prompt": "How do I completely delete all Adobe CS6 files on my Mac?",
  "response": "To completely delete all Adobe CS6 files from your Mac, you will need to uninstall the applications and then remove any associated files that are left behind. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide:\n\n### Step 1: Uninstall Adobe CS6 Applications\n\n1. **Use the Adobe Uninstaller:**\n   - Go to **Applications > Adobe Utilities > Adobe Installers**.\n   - Locate and run the **Uninstall Adobe Creative Suite 6** application.\n   - Follow the prompts to uninstall each application you had installed (like Photoshop, Illustrator, etc.).\n\n2. **Manually Remove Remaining Applications (if necessary):**\n   - Open **Finder** and navigate to **Applications**.\n   - Look for any remaining Adobe CS6 applications and drag them to the Trash.\n\n### Step 2: Delete Adobe CS6 Support Files\n\nEven after uninstallation, some files may remain on your system. To remove them:\n\n1. **Check Library Folders:**\n   - Open **Finder** and click **Go** in the menu bar. Hold down the **Option** key and select **Library**.\n   - Search the following locations and delete any Adobe-related folders or files:\n     - **Application Support/Adobe**\n     - **Preferences/Adobe**\n     - **Caches/Adobe**\n     - **Saved Application State/com.adobe.***\n\n2. **Remove Adobe Flash Player (if necessary):**\n   - If you have Adobe Flash Player installed, you can also uninstall it by downloading the uninstaller from Adobe\u2019s website and following the instructions.\n\n### Step 3: Empty the Trash\n\n1. **Empty the Trash:**\n   - Right-click on the Trash icon in your Dock and select **Empty Trash** to permanently remove all files.\n\n### Additional Steps (if needed)\n\n- You may also want to search for any additional Adobe-related files:\n  - Use Finder's search function: Enter \"Adobe\" in the search bar and make sure to search \"This Mac\" rather than just the current folder.\n  - Check for any additional items or folders that may not have been in the standard locations.\n\n### Important Notes\n\n- **Backup Important Files:** Before removing anything, make sure to back up important files to avoid accidental loss of data.\n- **Be Cautious with Library:** The Library folder contains system and application files; be careful not to delete anything you are not sure of.\n\nFollowing these steps should help you completely remove all Adobe CS6 files from your Mac.",
